This installer requires the Myth original CD-ROM or the Myth original floppies (3).
It will need 0.5MB of chipmem and 1.5MB of other mem to run the HD version, but
more memory is welcome.

If the game runs too fast, or freezes from time to time, try the NOFAST option.
You'll need 1MB of chipmem and 512K more fastmem.

FEATURES:

- Runs fully from HD/RAM, even on a standard A1200
- Convenient installer script
- Patched to avoid freezes on 68020+
- Uses JOTDStartup (JST) not included. Get it from aminet or my W3 page.
- Levelskip key (HELP)
- Quit key (F10)
- Trainer mode (TRAINER tooltype)

If you've got plenty of memory, don't set HDLOAD or LOWMEM. If you've got 2MB of fastmem,
set HDLOAD to be able to play. And finall if you only have got 2MB of chipmem (A1200),
select LOWMEM. The game will load frequently but you'll be able to play.

No more need to set NOFAST in this version. I try to use 24 bit of memory as extension mem.

INSTALLATION:

Follow the installation procedure with the installer script provided.
After that, click on the MythHD icon in your game directory to run the game.


BUGS:

